{
  "text": "Mangasarian [CITATION_1] introduced the concept of second and higher-order duality for nonlinear programming problems, which motivates several authors [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] in this field. The study of second and higher-order duality is significant due to the computational advantage over the first-order duality as it provides tighter bounds for the value of the objective function when approximations are used.",
  "citation_candidates": [
    "31415896",
    "120423563",
